teximage.text: $$ \textbf{Putnam 1966, B-1} \\ \\ \begin{aligned} &\text{Let a convex polygon } P \text{ be contained in a square of side 1. Show that the sum} \\ &\text{of the squares of the sides of } P \text{ is less than or equal to 4.} \end{aligned} $$

layer.text:
Clearly, this is NOT true of CONCAVE polygons, since a zigzag pattern could enable arbitrary large perimeters.
To show it of CONVEX polygons, we use to the Pythagorean theorem of squares and a "sub-division" principle.
